FBIS3-38688 "drweu025_h_94024" FBIS-WEU-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 GERMANY Communications, Entertainment Firms Plan Pay Television AU0402153094 Berlin DIE WELT in German 4 Feb 93 p 13 AU0402153094 Berlin DIE WELT Language: German Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Telekom, ZDF, Kirch, and Bertelsmann Establish Pay Television Station"] [Text] Frankfurt/Main -- With the entertainment concern Bertelsmann AG, the Munich film trader Leo Kirch, the Multimedia Market, and ZDF, German Telekom wants to get into the growing pay television business. This was reported by Telekom Executive Board member Dieter Gallist. Telekom thinks that 19 million households in Germany are now "qualified for pay television" -- but only 5 percent are subscribers to pay television. The share is already 17 percent in France and 55 percent in England, it was stated.
